# Machine-specific monitor configuration
# 
# This file uses safe defaults that work on any system.
# Customize locally for your setup - changes won't be committed to git (see .gitignore)
#
# CONFIGURATION OPTIONS:
# 1. Use nwg-displays (GUI tool) - will overwrite this file
# 2. Edit manually using examples below
#
# EXAMPLES:
# Single monitor:
#   monitor=DP-1,1920x1080@60,0x0,1.0
#
# Multiple monitors (side-by-side):
#   monitor=DP-1,2560x1440@144,0x0,1.0
#   monitor=HDMI-A-1,1920x1080@60,2560x0,1.0
#
# Laptop with HiDPI:
#   monitor=eDP-1,1920x1080@60,0x0,1.5
#
# Find your monitor names with: hyprctl monitors

# Default: Use preferred resolution for all monitors (safe for any system)
monitor=,preferred,auto,1
